WEBVTT

00:08.809 --> 00:10.711
HOMER:
Make way!

00:10.777 --> 00:12.779
(grunts)
D'oh!

00:14.081 --> 00:16.049
Get ready for fun, kids.

00:16.116 --> 00:18.619
Fun that begins with sunblock.

00:20.153 --> 00:22.789
(humming)

00:22.856 --> 00:24.324
Come on, Maggie.

00:24.391 --> 00:27.194
You don't want to grow up
to look like Grampa.

00:31.064 --> 00:34.101
Ugh, I can't enjoy seeing
animals treated like this.

00:34.167 --> 00:35.903
It must be horrible
spending every day

00:35.969 --> 00:37.571
trapped behind a pane of glass.

00:37.638 --> 00:39.306
It ain't great.

00:39.373 --> 00:41.808
Sweetie, if they're so unhappy,

00:41.875 --> 00:43.610
why are they wagging
their tails?

00:43.677 --> 00:47.180
‐That's how fish swim.
‐Well, I say they're happy.

00:47.247 --> 00:50.851
Penguin funerals
at 12:00, 2:00 and 4:00.

00:50.918 --> 00:52.920
("Tailgate Ramble" playing)

00:57.691 --> 01:00.794
The killer whale is called
an apex predator

01:00.861 --> 01:03.130
because there's nothing
that can eat it.

01:03.196 --> 01:05.632
Nothing that can eat it, eh?

01:05.699 --> 01:07.701
♪ ♪

01:10.637 --> 01:12.639
(laughs)

01:18.145 --> 01:20.047
No. No.

01:25.252 --> 01:27.988
This just got weird.

01:28.055 --> 01:31.224
And now for our biggest star,
it's lunchtime.

01:31.291 --> 01:33.260
I need a small child out here.

01:34.628 --> 01:36.196
You get on out there,
Hors D'oeuvre.

01:36.263 --> 01:40.000
(cheering)

01:40.067 --> 01:41.201
(all gasping)

01:41.268 --> 01:44.137
No worries, folks.
I lost my arm years ago.

01:44.204 --> 01:45.906
(laughter)

01:45.973 --> 01:47.207
Can we please go home?

01:47.274 --> 01:50.911
This "fun" place
is about to make me cry.

01:50.978 --> 01:53.146
Homer, why don't you take Maggie
for a stroll

01:53.213 --> 01:56.249
and we'll check out
that mermaid over there.

01:57.317 --> 01:59.586
Oh, that tail is so fake.

02:02.189 --> 02:04.191
(laughter)

02:05.459 --> 02:07.194
Smithers,
can we splash the people

02:07.260 --> 02:10.063
‐dining at that fine restaurant?
‐As you wish, sir.

02:11.698 --> 02:13.634
(screaming)

02:13.700 --> 02:15.335
I love Sunday fun.

02:15.402 --> 02:16.703
Mm...

02:16.770 --> 02:19.239
You know, sweetie,
I always wanted a boat,

02:19.306 --> 02:22.309
but my dad could
never afford one.

02:22.376 --> 02:25.212
♪ <i>Sitting on the dock</i>
<i>of the bay</i> ♪

02:25.278 --> 02:29.449
♪ <i>Missing all my school today</i> ♪

02:29.516 --> 02:33.120
♪ <i>Getting dumb...</i> ♪

02:33.186 --> 02:35.188
(whistling)

02:37.190 --> 02:38.759
Knock off that whistling.

02:38.825 --> 02:42.529
Men have good times in silence.

02:42.596 --> 02:45.132
Daddy, will we ever get a boat?

02:45.198 --> 02:46.933
Are you kidding?

02:47.000 --> 02:49.269
We couldn't even afford worms.

02:49.336 --> 02:51.071
Oh...

02:51.138 --> 02:53.073
‐(sniffling)
‐Aw, don't cry.

02:53.140 --> 02:55.075
Have some Scottish
feel‐good juice.

02:55.142 --> 02:57.077
Okay.

02:57.144 --> 02:59.946
‐(grunts, coughs)
‐Come on. Drink up.

03:00.013 --> 03:01.481
‐(whimpers)
‐(chuckles)

03:01.548 --> 03:04.951
By the standards of the day,
I'm a great father.

03:05.018 --> 03:06.153
Mm...

03:07.854 --> 03:09.589
Nice boat, huh? I sell boats.

03:09.656 --> 03:11.191
Wish you could have one?

03:11.258 --> 03:12.559
Yeah, but I'll never own a boat.

03:12.626 --> 03:15.529
It's just a dream,
like doing a sit‐up.

03:15.595 --> 03:17.531
(chuckles)
Don't be so sure.

03:17.597 --> 03:19.533
I don't know what you do
for a living, but me?

03:19.599 --> 03:21.568
I'm in the dream business.

03:21.635 --> 03:24.204
I thought you sold boats.
Make up your mind, liar.

03:24.271 --> 03:27.140
(laughs) Now I could get
in big trouble for doing this,

03:27.207 --> 03:29.409
but if you buy this boat now
for the listed price,

03:29.476 --> 03:31.712
I'll throw in
this genuine captain's hat.

03:31.778 --> 03:33.146
Don't tell my manager.

03:33.213 --> 03:34.981
What do you think I am,
an idiot?

03:35.048 --> 03:37.017
This hat isn't even adjustable.

03:37.084 --> 03:39.086
‐It's one‐size‐fits‐all.
‐Deal.

03:39.152 --> 03:41.855
Wha‐‐ No, wait,
my wife will kill me.

03:41.922 --> 03:43.356
You think your wife's
gonna kill you

03:43.423 --> 03:45.859
when she's sipping margaritas
as the sun sets,

03:45.926 --> 03:48.662
her hair blowing softly
in the ocean breeze?

03:48.729 --> 03:51.198
Her hair doesn't blow.
It kind of clangs.

03:51.264 --> 03:53.333
Look, ask any financial planner
and they'll tell you

03:53.400 --> 03:55.135
that getting a boat
is a better investment

03:55.202 --> 03:58.038
than getting a divorce
or opening a bookstore.

03:58.105 --> 03:59.806
One more thing
and I'm convinced.

03:59.873 --> 04:02.542
I'll give you this little pin
from a defunct yacht club.

04:02.609 --> 04:04.044
Sold.

04:04.111 --> 04:06.313
Hey, uh, what's this little
hook thing on it?

04:06.379 --> 04:09.516
That's an anchor. You're gonna
be a fine yachtsman.

04:10.684 --> 04:12.152
(moans)

04:12.219 --> 04:16.656
(gasps) Oh, my God,
your dorsal fin has collapsed.

04:16.723 --> 04:20.026
Don't you see? She doesn't have
enough space to swim.

04:20.093 --> 04:22.095
That thing <i>is</i> huge.

04:25.165 --> 04:27.134
This park is cruel and inhumane.

04:27.200 --> 04:29.669
Empty the tanks. Pull the plug!

04:29.736 --> 04:32.172
I'll be back.
You can't silence me.

04:32.239 --> 04:36.276
I‐‐ aw. So cute.

04:36.343 --> 04:40.647
(sighs) Thrown out
of another amusement park.

04:40.714 --> 04:43.550
‐Take me with you.
‐Not enough seat belts.

04:45.652 --> 04:47.087
♪ <i>What do you do</i>
<i>with a drunken salesman?</i> ♪

04:47.154 --> 04:48.889
♪ <i>He goes home to his wife.</i> ♪

04:48.955 --> 04:51.024
Finally moved
that old cabin cruiser.

04:51.091 --> 04:53.026
No one spots a sucker like you.

04:53.093 --> 04:56.096
Let me guess: overweight guy,
midlife crisis?

04:56.163 --> 04:57.330
Mm. The kind of fat
where you don't even know

04:57.397 --> 04:58.732
how old they are.

04:58.799 --> 05:00.767
‐How was your day?
‐Beautiful.

05:00.834 --> 05:03.703
Sold a Jacuzzi to someone
who came in to use the phone.

05:03.770 --> 05:05.205
Did you gouge him
on the dipping attachment?

05:05.272 --> 05:07.174
Wholesale plus three grand.

05:07.240 --> 05:09.342
Ooh. You get over here.

05:09.409 --> 05:12.179
(chuckles)
Make me an offer.

05:12.245 --> 05:13.880
(both laugh)

05:13.947 --> 05:15.182
Smooth.

05:16.149 --> 05:17.551
Bart, I need your help...

05:17.617 --> 05:20.053
(groaning):
Go away.

05:20.120 --> 05:22.522
‐ ...with a prank.
‐Oh, what do you need?

05:22.589 --> 05:25.759
Hot sauce? Cow heart? Fire ants?

05:25.826 --> 05:27.327
Oh. They're gone.

05:27.394 --> 05:30.030
How could fire ants
get out of a paper bag?

05:30.096 --> 05:33.366
Thank you, Lord, for these
fire ants entering my nose,

05:33.433 --> 05:36.169
biting my brain,
testing my faith.

05:36.236 --> 05:37.938
But I will...
(shouts)

05:38.004 --> 05:39.506
Damn it, where's the spray?

05:41.775 --> 05:44.544
Thanks for helping us
free that whale, Willie.

05:44.611 --> 05:48.415
Aye. Now, to put on
me camouflage.

05:51.051 --> 05:53.286
Man, you really know this place.

05:53.353 --> 05:55.155
I work here in the summer.

05:55.222 --> 05:57.924
Unlike you children,
the fish don't make fun of me.

05:57.991 --> 06:00.493
(squeaking)

06:00.560 --> 06:02.162
Just 'cause you're cuter than me

06:02.229 --> 06:04.197
don't mean you're better
than me.

06:04.264 --> 06:05.999
You're not even a fish!

06:06.066 --> 06:08.101
(squeaking)

06:08.168 --> 06:12.105
Unless I miss me guess, these
are the orca tank controls.

06:12.172 --> 06:13.940
(whispers):
This guy's good.

06:14.007 --> 06:17.944
We'll open the seawater gate and
she'll go straight in the ocean.

06:18.011 --> 06:20.447
(grunting)

06:20.513 --> 06:23.617
Uh, I believe it's lefty loosey.

06:23.683 --> 06:28.455
Everything in this country
is backwards and wrong.

06:28.521 --> 06:30.523
♪ ♪

06:44.037 --> 06:47.040
Thank God. A way off the ship.

06:49.709 --> 06:52.646
We did it.
We set a captive animal free.

06:52.712 --> 06:55.882
Pretty cool, huh, Bart?

06:55.949 --> 06:57.684
Look how happy that thing is.

06:57.751 --> 06:59.686
Lis, this is a new feeling.

06:59.753 --> 07:03.423
We helped a whale be free
and now I feel wonderful.

07:03.490 --> 07:06.226
What you're searching for
is "altruism."

07:06.293 --> 07:08.228
‐(grunts)
‐Ow.

07:08.295 --> 07:10.830
And that's called karma.

07:10.897 --> 07:12.632
Are you happy, Willie?

07:12.699 --> 07:15.435
I'll show you. Air bagpipes.

07:15.502 --> 07:17.504
(imitating bagpipe)

07:28.214 --> 07:29.983
Okay, I'm gonna take
the blindfold off.

07:30.050 --> 07:31.618
Don't ask questions.
Don't probe for answers.

07:31.685 --> 07:33.820
I'll just pretend
I don't know we're on a dock

07:33.887 --> 07:35.188
next to the water.

07:35.255 --> 07:38.725
Look where we are.
A dock next to the water.

07:38.792 --> 07:41.528
Aw. You got a boat for the day.

07:41.594 --> 07:43.997
Did you bring beer
and sandwiches?

07:44.064 --> 07:47.067
Why don't you open that?

07:47.133 --> 07:50.403
Hey, Midge, got your beer
and sandwiches right here.

07:50.470 --> 07:54.040
♪ ♪

07:54.107 --> 07:57.043
Come on, Maggie, get on Daddy's
<i>wap</i> and take the wheel.

07:57.110 --> 07:59.145
That's right, maximum <i>thwottle.</i>

07:59.212 --> 08:01.181
(motor revs)

08:01.247 --> 08:03.183
Vroom, vroom.
Maximum <i>thwottle.</i>

08:03.249 --> 08:06.553
Ooh, you're <i>hydwopwaning.</i>
Yes, you are.

08:06.619 --> 08:08.955
Whoo‐hoo!

08:11.024 --> 08:13.126
Whoo‐hoo!

08:13.193 --> 08:18.565
88 years old
and never learned to swim.

08:18.631 --> 08:22.168
♪ ♪

08:22.235 --> 08:24.371
What a wonderful day, Homie.

08:24.437 --> 08:27.374
It's like we're living
in the painting over our couch.

08:27.440 --> 08:29.376
<i>HOMER:</i>
<i>Our marriage</i>
<i>has never been better.</i>

08:29.442 --> 08:31.077
<i>Time to risk it all.</i>

08:31.144 --> 08:33.947
Okay, guess whose boat this is.

08:34.014 --> 08:35.749
I hope it's not Johnny Depp's.

08:35.815 --> 08:38.351
He's already in
so much financial trouble.

08:38.418 --> 08:41.721
Brace yourself, baby. It's ours.

08:41.788 --> 08:44.090
(gasps)
You bought this boat?

08:44.157 --> 08:46.092
No. We bought this boat.

08:46.159 --> 08:48.261
You just weren't aware.

08:48.328 --> 08:50.196
(grunts, exhales)

08:50.263 --> 08:53.099
‐You know what? It's okay.
‐Are you nuts?

08:53.166 --> 08:56.369
You went out and got something
the whole family could enjoy.

08:56.436 --> 08:58.371
‐Let's live a little.
‐Oh, my God, Marge.

08:58.438 --> 08:59.973
What's happened to you?

09:00.040 --> 09:01.975
I admit it.
You've worn me down.

09:02.042 --> 09:04.811
You're my little polished gem.

09:04.878 --> 09:07.247
Aw. Mwah.

09:09.115 --> 09:11.584
(chuckles)
What do you think, Dad?

09:11.651 --> 09:15.255
(crying): Oh, you did it, son.
You actually did it.

09:15.321 --> 09:18.958
You found a parking spot
at the marina.

09:19.025 --> 09:23.029
‐Oh, I never...
‐No, Dad. I got a boat.

09:23.096 --> 09:26.399
‐Get on.
‐Oh, sure. I‐‐ Wait a minute.

09:26.466 --> 09:29.202
You're gonna kill me
and dump me overboard.

09:29.269 --> 09:31.137
Well, fine. Here's my will.

09:31.204 --> 09:32.972
HOMER:
Oh, come on now,

09:33.039 --> 09:34.407
I'm not gonna kill you.

09:34.474 --> 09:35.975
That's 'cause you're a lazy bum.

09:36.042 --> 09:38.211
Now, come on, give me a hug.

09:38.278 --> 09:39.512
‐Ooh.
‐Aw.

09:41.748 --> 09:43.049
(motor clattering, backfiring)

09:45.485 --> 09:47.787
‐Nice boat.
‐I'm the owner.

09:47.854 --> 09:51.024
Very nice. I must tell you,
she's running a little rough.

09:51.091 --> 09:53.193
(laughs)
Aren't we all?

09:53.259 --> 09:54.461
(chuckles)
Good one.

09:54.527 --> 09:55.995
Listen, uh, I'm a mechanic,

09:56.062 --> 09:58.264
and I think you're going
to need my help.

09:58.331 --> 10:01.034
Your boat is used,
and it needs repairs now.

10:01.101 --> 10:02.302
Why now?

10:02.368 --> 10:04.838
‐It's sinking.
‐(shrieks)

10:04.904 --> 10:07.874
So, Milhouse, it turns out
I'm addicted to altruism.

10:07.941 --> 10:10.276
I'm not gonna be happy
till I set another animal free.

10:10.343 --> 10:14.147
If I wanted to hang out with
Lisa, I'd hang out with Lisa.

10:14.214 --> 10:15.915
No, you wouldn't.

10:15.982 --> 10:17.650
Now I can't free another fish

10:17.717 --> 10:19.719
because they've increased
security at the water park.

10:19.786 --> 10:22.055
This is great.
I got a flashlight,

10:22.122 --> 10:24.858
walkie‐talkie,
big old ring of keys.

10:24.924 --> 10:27.927
But I found something else
we can set free.

10:27.994 --> 10:30.230
<i>NARRATOR:</i>
<i>Meet LoLo the gorilla.</i>

10:30.296 --> 10:32.265
<i>Powerful, intelligent.</i>

10:32.332 --> 10:34.234
<i>She can sign five words.</i>

10:34.300 --> 10:36.736
<i>"Friend," "enemy," "kill,"</i>

10:36.803 --> 10:39.339
<i>"vodka" and "Seinfeld."</i>

10:39.405 --> 10:41.107
You know she wants out.

10:41.174 --> 10:43.710
Now for security,
I'll say the rest in Pig Latin.

10:43.776 --> 10:45.945
Ee‐way, ill‐way, oh‐gay, oh‐tay,
ee‐thay, oo‐zay.

10:46.012 --> 10:47.380
We're going on eBay?

10:47.447 --> 10:50.250
Ay‐yay arumba‐cay.

10:50.316 --> 10:51.718
<i>(phone rings)</i>

10:51.784 --> 10:54.320
‐Yello.
‐Are you sitting down?

10:54.387 --> 10:55.622
Of course.

10:55.688 --> 10:57.724
Fixed your boat.
Here's the total.

10:57.790 --> 10:59.726
Don't say I didn't warn you.

11:01.327 --> 11:03.897
There is one hope:
share your expenses.

11:03.963 --> 11:05.899
Pull your friends
into the black hole with you.

11:05.965 --> 11:08.868
Yes, sir. You're supposed to
disappear now.

11:08.935 --> 11:11.204
Yeah, I will,
but that's another hundred.

11:11.271 --> 11:12.438
D'oh!

11:15.008 --> 11:16.943
(sighs)

11:17.010 --> 11:18.778
‐Hey, Homer.
‐What's the problem?

11:18.845 --> 11:23.716
(sighs) I feel terrible,
just terrible.

11:23.783 --> 11:25.218
Oh, yeah? Why's that?

11:25.285 --> 11:26.486
Because I have been withholding

11:26.553 --> 11:29.923
an incredible opportunity
from you guys.

11:29.989 --> 11:32.058
My apologies. Got to go.

11:32.125 --> 11:34.394
Did I hear, "Wait, wait"?

11:34.460 --> 11:35.762
‐No.
‐We're good.

11:35.828 --> 11:40.099
Okay, 'cause it's
really, really incredible.

11:40.166 --> 11:43.469
See you. Leaving now. On my way.

11:43.536 --> 11:45.939
Last chance. Buh‐bye.

11:46.005 --> 11:49.075
Eh? Eh?

11:51.211 --> 11:52.946
Eh?

11:53.012 --> 11:55.014
(phone rings)

11:55.081 --> 11:56.282
Yello.

11:56.349 --> 11:58.518
Okay, I'll bite.
What's the opportunity?

11:58.585 --> 11:59.786
I don't know, Lenny.

11:59.852 --> 12:02.655
I mean, I need someone
with genuine enthusiasm.

12:02.722 --> 12:05.091
‐Understood. Have a good ni...
‐Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

12:05.158 --> 12:06.626
Do you want to go in
on a boat with me?

12:06.693 --> 12:08.061
We share expenses,
we split the time.

12:08.127 --> 12:09.896
If you agree,
continue breathing normally.

12:09.963 --> 12:11.231
I don't know.

12:11.297 --> 12:13.166
I heard that sharing boats
can ruin friendships.

12:13.233 --> 12:16.135
Well, somebody better tell Carl
'cause he is in.

12:16.202 --> 12:18.071
Wait, I don't want
to be left out. I'm in!

12:18.137 --> 12:20.773
(chuckles) Glad to hear it.
Could you put Carl on?

12:20.840 --> 12:22.075
(chuckles)

12:25.278 --> 12:27.046
We brought
our old college stereo.

12:27.113 --> 12:28.381
Let's let everyone
in the water know

12:28.448 --> 12:31.184
some big shots
are having a wild time.

12:31.251 --> 12:34.387
♪ <i>I love to work</i>
<i>at nothing all day</i> ♪

12:34.454 --> 12:37.190
♪ <i>And I'll be taking care</i>
<i>of business</i> ♪

12:37.257 --> 12:39.125
♪ <i>Every day</i> ♪

12:39.192 --> 12:40.493
(muffled):
♪ <i>Taking care of business</i> ♪

12:40.560 --> 12:42.228
♪ <i>Every way...</i> ♪

12:42.295 --> 12:46.065
Yeah, those fish are hearing
some awesome B. T. O. right now.

12:46.132 --> 12:49.068
Why don't you take
the throttle, dear.

12:49.135 --> 12:50.236
(motor revs)

12:50.303 --> 12:53.406
Oh, I feel it!
I feel the power.

12:53.473 --> 12:56.009
You know, I thought we were
just dating casually.

12:56.075 --> 13:00.146
It wasn't going anywhere.
But now, will you marry me?

13:00.213 --> 13:03.549
(stammers) I, uh...
This is not a no!

13:05.218 --> 13:07.020
♪ <i>Taking care of business</i> ♪

13:07.086 --> 13:08.121
♪ <i>Every day.</i> ♪

13:08.187 --> 13:09.522
(elephant trumpets)

13:11.524 --> 13:13.126
Okay, I've got it.

13:13.192 --> 13:16.729
What she doesn't know is there's
an overgrown vine behind her

13:16.796 --> 13:18.998
where she can climb up
to freedom.

13:19.065 --> 13:22.635
One of us has to get in there
and show her how to do it,

13:22.702 --> 13:25.171
but which one?

13:25.238 --> 13:28.074
Uh, did I ever mention that
I'm allergic to gorilla fur?

13:28.141 --> 13:31.944
Dang! The one thing
I'm not allergic to.

13:32.011 --> 13:35.214
You know, this time I really
thought Bart was gonna do it.

13:35.281 --> 13:38.951
‐I'll do it next time.
‐I know you will, buddy.

13:39.018 --> 13:41.521
‐(LoLo roars)
‐Ah! Oh!

13:41.587 --> 13:43.489
(panting)

13:45.591 --> 13:47.193
(Milhouse whimpers)

13:47.260 --> 13:49.295
♪ ♪

13:51.264 --> 13:53.933
(roaring)

14:06.145 --> 14:08.047
We got a problem.

14:08.114 --> 14:10.183
Two problems.

14:10.249 --> 14:13.820
So this is what it's like
to be in a loving family.

14:20.426 --> 14:22.695
♪ ♪

14:22.762 --> 14:23.930
(buzzing)

14:23.996 --> 14:27.900
‐(phone buzzing)
‐(groans)

14:27.967 --> 14:29.135
Hello?

14:29.202 --> 14:30.903
Lis, altruism sucks.

14:30.970 --> 14:32.572
You idiot.

14:32.638 --> 14:35.808
You set a fish free because
it has an ocean to swim in.

14:35.875 --> 14:37.310
If you set a gorilla free,

14:37.377 --> 14:41.514
it goes into the city
and it gets killed.

14:41.581 --> 14:43.116
<i>"The Great Esc‐Ape"?</i>

14:43.182 --> 14:45.585
<i>A gorilla mysteriously freed</i>
<i>from the Springfield Zoo</i>

14:45.651 --> 14:47.987
<i>is wreaking havoc</i>
<i>all over town.</i>

14:48.054 --> 14:50.189
<i>The police, as always,</i>
<i>are useless.</i>

14:50.256 --> 14:52.992
<i>WIGGUM:</i>
<i>Not true, Kent.</i>
<i>We've located the gorilla.</i>

14:53.059 --> 14:55.628
<i>He's on the top of a store</i>
<i>next to a sign reading,</i>

14:55.695 --> 14:58.030
<i>"You'll Go Ape</i>
<i>For Our Bargains."</i>

14:58.097 --> 15:00.133
Uh, yeah, I think that's
a balloon, Chief.

15:00.199 --> 15:01.634
Prove it.

15:01.701 --> 15:03.236
‐(air hissing)
‐Happy, Lou?

15:03.302 --> 15:04.937
You just shot a balloon.

15:05.004 --> 15:07.106
I love boat ownership.

15:07.173 --> 15:10.176
Spending every weekend
polishing brass.

15:10.243 --> 15:11.844
I feel like Larry Ellison.

15:11.911 --> 15:14.447
I had the espresso maker
mounted on gimbals,

15:14.514 --> 15:17.083
so when the big waves hit,
they won't ruin the foam art

15:17.150 --> 15:18.751
on our cappuccino.

15:21.521 --> 15:24.023
Foam Lenny, you're my hero.

15:24.090 --> 15:26.626
Hey, who are all these people?

15:26.692 --> 15:29.495
I, uh, may have sold
some extra shares,

15:29.562 --> 15:31.998
so I'm afraid
these are all co‐owners.

15:32.064 --> 15:35.435
Co‐owner I be, says me. Yarr.

15:35.501 --> 15:38.604
Duffman wants to impress
his new stepkids.

15:38.671 --> 15:40.106
What do you think, Kyle?

15:40.173 --> 15:43.142
My father died
from drinking your product.

15:43.209 --> 15:46.045
We have a lot to work on.
Oh, yeah!

15:46.112 --> 15:49.582
All these people are co‐owners?
Even Cat Lady?

15:49.649 --> 15:52.084
Now she's Catamaran Lady.

15:52.151 --> 15:54.387
‐(loud music playing)
‐(overlapping chatter)

15:54.454 --> 15:56.422
There's too many people,
I can't move.

15:56.489 --> 15:58.090
Okay, cast off.

16:05.064 --> 16:06.632
Hey, my cappuccino head.

16:06.699 --> 16:10.102
Well, at least I can swim
to shore. (panting)

16:10.169 --> 16:13.539
Eh, eh, this is,
this is too hard.

16:13.606 --> 16:16.008
Hey! Hey, I can stand!

16:16.075 --> 16:17.977
Eh, no, it's just too hard.

16:24.484 --> 16:26.219
Perhaps music
will calm her down.

16:26.285 --> 16:29.155
♪ <i>One, eight, seven, seven,</i>
<i>cars for kids.</i> ♪

16:29.222 --> 16:32.124
(roaring)

16:33.159 --> 16:34.760
Ah! My screenplay!

16:34.827 --> 16:36.729
LoLo. LoLo!

16:36.796 --> 16:38.264
"Friend." "Friend."

16:38.331 --> 16:39.899
(roars)

16:39.966 --> 16:42.902
Oh, no, I accidentally
signed "fiend."

16:42.969 --> 16:47.073
‐Look, I'll help you
find safety.
‐(sniffing)

16:47.139 --> 16:50.610
I just have to convince you
I'm your friend. How?

16:50.676 --> 16:52.144
How?

16:54.146 --> 16:57.049
<i>(Seinfeld</i> theme music playing)

16:57.116 --> 16:59.218
(gasps) <i>Seinfeld.</i>

16:59.285 --> 17:02.288
‐(roars)
‐Newman.

17:04.757 --> 17:07.159
If this was just
a little bit looser,

17:07.226 --> 17:11.063
it would be the best thing
in the world. (chuckles)

17:11.130 --> 17:12.732
(sighs)

17:12.798 --> 17:15.835
Sir, I would like
to return my boat

17:15.902 --> 17:18.004
for a full refund.

17:18.070 --> 17:20.006
Oh, I'm sorry.
Perhaps James Cameron

17:20.072 --> 17:21.874
would take an interest
in your sunken ship,

17:21.941 --> 17:24.877
but my responsibility
ended at ka‐ching.

17:24.944 --> 17:26.812
You sold me a lemon.

17:26.879 --> 17:29.248
Mm‐hmm, people like lemons.
They're good for your voice.

17:29.315 --> 17:32.752
With your smooth talk, you could
convince anyone of anything.

17:32.818 --> 17:35.454
You like my lapels?
You want to buy the jacket?

17:35.521 --> 17:38.591
‐Yes.
‐(chuckles) 50 bucks.

17:38.658 --> 17:40.893
(laughs)
Now if you'll excuse me,

17:40.960 --> 17:42.128
I'm also in another business:

17:42.194 --> 17:43.963
smuggling meth
inside bicycle tires.

17:44.030 --> 17:45.932
Thanks for the free bike.

17:45.998 --> 17:47.967
Just get it to Mexico
by tomorrow.

17:48.034 --> 17:49.635
Ba‐ja!

17:49.702 --> 17:51.938
MARGE:
Lisa, what are you doing?

17:52.004 --> 17:54.473
Um, I'm in my bedroom with Dad.

17:54.540 --> 17:57.376
‐Oh, that's sweet.
‐(bottle shatters)

17:57.443 --> 17:59.211
‐FLANDERS: Watch it!
‐Oh.

17:59.278 --> 18:02.715
Homie, I told you
to stop doing that.

18:05.117 --> 18:06.285
<i>Y'all bring your gorilla here.</i>

18:06.352 --> 18:08.087
<i>We'll teach him</i>
<i>to ride and shoot,</i>

18:08.154 --> 18:10.089
<i>and soon it'll be</i>
<i>a</i> Planet of the Apes.

18:10.156 --> 18:11.090
<i>Whoops.</i>

18:11.157 --> 18:12.825
No.

18:12.892 --> 18:14.994
<i>Here at U. T. A.,</i>
<i>United Talented Apes,</i>

18:15.061 --> 18:16.596
<i>we'll shave your gorilla</i>

18:16.662 --> 18:19.065
<i>and make him a body double</i>
<i>for Bruce Willis,</i>

18:19.131 --> 18:20.900
<i>and if he behaves</i>
<i>even a little,</i>

18:20.967 --> 18:23.102
<i>he could become Bruce Willis.</i>

18:23.169 --> 18:25.972
Next. Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

18:26.038 --> 18:29.141
You're perfect.
Will you take my ape?

18:30.776 --> 18:34.447
Dr. Goodall, I can't thank you
enough for saving LoLo.

18:34.513 --> 18:37.283
LoLo. That's what they
called her in captivity,

18:37.350 --> 18:39.151
but I've given her a new name,

18:39.218 --> 18:43.322
one worthy of such
a magnificent creature: PoPo.

18:43.389 --> 18:46.692
And may I just tell you,
you've always been my hero.

18:46.759 --> 18:48.628
Thank you. But I wonder,

18:48.694 --> 18:52.398
how many female scientists
have you told they're your hero?

18:52.465 --> 18:55.301
In your field? Um, only three.

18:55.368 --> 18:59.205
Oh, well. Good enough.
We'll take fine care of PoPo.

18:59.271 --> 19:01.374
‐See you soon.
‐Wait. Come back.

19:01.440 --> 19:04.343
Take me with you. I want a life
exactly like yours.

19:04.410 --> 19:08.214
Well, so do hundreds of others,
but still, you might get lucky

19:08.280 --> 19:11.517
if you work really hard
and get a doctorate.

19:11.584 --> 19:13.052
Would you give me a scholarship?

19:13.119 --> 19:15.955
No, you'd have to save up,
like I did.

19:16.022 --> 19:17.957
Then there's a slight chance
you'll have me?

19:18.024 --> 19:21.160
Well, very slight,
but don't give up.

19:21.227 --> 19:24.163
That is the most encouraging
thing I have ever heard.

19:24.230 --> 19:26.666
Lis, thanks for undoing
the damage of my good deed.

19:26.732 --> 19:28.734
I'm glad you've
come to understand

19:28.801 --> 19:30.870
the importance of altruism.

19:30.936 --> 19:32.538
Altruism rocks!

19:32.605 --> 19:35.374
Like when you let something go
and it smashes everything.

19:35.441 --> 19:37.343
Next, I want to
altruism a rhino.

19:37.410 --> 19:40.746
Then I'm gonna altruism a robot
with sledgehammers for hands.

19:40.813 --> 19:42.615
Sometimes I just want
to sit back

19:42.682 --> 19:46.552
and watch the whole world
altruism.

19:46.619 --> 19:49.388
Look, the gorillas
have picked up some new habits

19:49.455 --> 19:50.856
from your father.

19:54.360 --> 19:57.063
Yeah, but Homer picked up
some cool gorilla moves, too.

19:57.129 --> 19:59.231
(grunting)

19:59.298 --> 20:00.933
Oh...

20:06.272 --> 20:09.308
‐Well, I never.
‐(angry chatter)

20:09.375 --> 20:11.110
Okay, okay, I know you're mad,

20:11.177 --> 20:13.245
but because there are
so many of us,

20:13.312 --> 20:15.147
we each just lost a little.

20:15.214 --> 20:17.950
And I just want to say,
for the rest of your life,

20:18.017 --> 20:21.153
you'll know that you're just as
good as someone who owns a boat

20:21.220 --> 20:24.323
because you owned a boat
for five minutes.

20:24.390 --> 20:27.960
Well, you did give us something
for our money: great memories.

20:28.027 --> 20:30.830
And look what someone in Japan
sent back to me.

20:30.896 --> 20:32.765
Three cheers for Homer.

20:32.832 --> 20:35.801
ALL:
Hip, hip, hooray!
Hip, hip, hooray!

20:35.868 --> 20:37.103
Hip, hip, hooray!

20:37.169 --> 20:39.371
<i>ANNOUNCER:</i>
Foam Lenny <i>on Fox!</i>

20:39.438 --> 20:43.075
<i>Fridays at 8:00,</i>
<i>because we've got nothing else.</i>

